article_title: With funds for physician training set to expire, rural doctor shortage persists
article_text: After two years as a medical school resident for the Puyallup Tribe of Indians, Aaron Rhyner sees 14 patients a day, works 50 to 80 hours each week and earns roughly $50,000 a year.
